NewsList.description:
In Ukraine, the Animal Help Ukraine platform was launched, where animal owners can get free online consultations with veterinarians from the USA, Canada, Great Britain and other countries of the world. Consultations with the veterinarian will take place in the chat, equipped with an automatic translator to overcome the language barrier. Ukrainians will be able to consult with professional veterinarians about:
nutrition - how to find alternatives to conventional feed in wartime and switch to natural products;
animal peace - how to reduce anxiety and stress of a pet during explosions;
first aid - how to save an animal in extreme conditions;
exotic animals - how to help those who need special care;
medicines - what to do in the absence of the necessary medicine and what "human" counterparts can be used to treat animals. The service also has its own library of materials and resources. There you can find care recommendations and advice on keeping pets healthy.
